The Judicial Commission of Inquiry into allegations of State Capture, Corruption and Fraud in the Public Sector including Organs of State continues. The Commission to hear Transnet related testimony from Christopher Todd. JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry hears Transnet-related testimony on Wednesday afternoon. The commission will hear from Christopher Todd. Todd is a director at Bowmans Gilfillan Attorneys. READ: State Capture Inquiry continues with Eskom related evidence Earlier in the day, the anticipated testimony of former Eskom CFO, Anoj Singh was postponed. Singh's lawyer has told the state capture inquiry that he is not yet in a position to give evidence.